node.text:
Took these photos a couple weeks ago when I hit the halfway point in my pregnancy and I can’t believe how much faster  this pregnancy is going! I’m starting to realize how quickly these twins are coming and the panic is setting in because I am not ready AT ALL!
Even though I’m stressed about almost everything when it comes to having these babies, one thing I don’t have to worry about is that I know we will be using @ViaCord to bank our babies’ cord blood. We did cord blood banking with Flynn when he was born, and it gave us such peace of mind during a time when everything felt stressful. So we will definitely be doing it again with the twins when they make their grand entrance. 
Cord Blood Banking is so cool! After the umbilical cord is cut the doctor collects the leftover blood inside of it, and then it’s shipped off to ViaCord where they extract the stem cells from the blood and freeze them for your family’s potential future medical use. So even though I feel like I have no idea what I’m doing most days, I can rest easy knowing we are doing something to help plan for our family’s future potential healthcare needs.
So, if you’re expecting, this is definitely something you should look into to give you one less thing to worry about. 
#CordBloodBanking
#PlanWithViaCord
#Sponsored

Flynn was so excited to play with all of the toys and watch the show. Mickey has always been a trusted friend for my toddler, and this new show brings so much fun to his day! Check it out on Disney Junior today!  #DisneyJunior #MickeyMouseFunhouse @disneyjunior

node.text:
if you ever get pregnant at the same time as your sister-in-law, i strongly recommend doing an awkward maternity photoshoot together. 

I’m 22 weeks pregnant now and jessica is almost 40 weeks! She’s about to pop! We filmed the process of getting these photos and between jessica almost going into labor and me holding back vomit, it’s a pretty ridiculous video. Go check it out on their youtube channel! After that, you can watch us stuff our faces in the mukbang I just uploaded to my channel! @jessicaballinger 🤰🏻🤰🏻

node.text: Still recovering from my virtual live show last weekend. So grateful to everyone who tuned in and watched the madness! I had a blast, but my body is still aching a week later. My body has basically shut down in order to grow them and make sure they are healthy and strong. I can barely walk, everything exhausts me, I have emotional breakdowns multiple times a day, everything hurts, and I feel like a useless shell of a human. Growing twins is no joke! Double the babies, double the symptoms! 🥴 But I’m halfway done and at the end of this year I get to meet my tiny little sweet son and daughter! AAAH! So exciting!
